# NSPrintOperation.PageOrder

**Enumeration**

Constants that specify the page order.

## Declaration

```swift
enum PageOrder
```

## Overview

These constants are used by [doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSPrintOperation/pageOrder-swift.property] and [doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSPrintOperation/pageOrder-swift.property].

## Constants

- **NSPrintOperation.PageOrder.ascendingPageOrder**: Ascending (back to front) page order.
- **NSPrintOperation.PageOrder.descendingPageOrder**: Descending (front to back) page order.
- **NSPrintOperation.PageOrder.specialPageOrder**: The spooler does not rearrange pages—they are printed in the order received by the spooler.
- **NSPrintOperation.PageOrder.unknownPageOrder**: No page order specified.

## Initializers

- **init(rawValue:)**

## Managing Page Information

- **currentPage**: The current page number being printed.
- **pageRange**: The range of pages associated with the print operation.
- **pageOrder**: The print order for the pages of the operation.

## Conforms To

- BitwiseCopyable
- Equatable
- Hashable
- RawRepresentable
- Sendable
- SendableMetatype
